---
// LocCounter — The quirky element
// Displays GitHub Lines of Code from loc-data.json
// Generated daily by GitHub Actions workflow (.github/workflows/loc-counter.yml)
// Shows a clean "awaiting sync" state until real data lands.
---

<div class="paper-card p-4 sm:p-5 font-code text-sm" id="loc-counter">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2 text-fg-muted">
    <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-accent animate-glow-pulse" />
    <span class="micro-label">Live Stats</span>
  </div>
  <div id="loc-content">
    <div class="text-fg-muted text-xs font-body animate-pulse">Loading...</div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  var content = document.getElementById("loc-content");

  function row(label, valueHtml, valueClass) {
    return '<div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">' +
      '<span class="text-fg-muted text-xs">' + label + '</span>' +
      '<span class="' + (valueClass || "text-fg text-lg font-bold font-display") + '">' + valueHtml + '</span>' +
    '</div>';
  }

  function sparklineBars(history, barClass) {
    return history.map(function (val) {
      var h = Math.max(3, (val / (Math.max.apply(null, history) || 1)) * 28);
      return '<div class="w-[6px] rounded-sm ' + barClass + '" style="height:' + h + 'px" title="' + val.toLocaleString() + '"></div>';
    }).join("");
  }

  function renderSeeded() {
    content.innerHTML =
      '<div class="space-y-2">' +
        row("~/$", "&mdash;", "text-fg-muted text-lg font-bold font-display") +
        '<div class="pt-2 border-t border-card-border">' +
          '<div class="flex items-end gap-[2px] h-8">' +
            Array.from({ length: 30 }, function () {
              return '<div class="w-[6px] rounded-sm bg-muted/40" style="height:3px"></div>';
            }).join("") +
          '</div>' +
        '</div>' +
        '<div class="text-fg-muted text-[10px] pt-1">Awaiting first GitHub Actions sync</div>' +
      '</div>';
  }

  async function loadLocData() {
    try {
      var res = await fetch("/loc-data.json");
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Not found");
      var data = await res.json();

      // Seeded / empty state — don't show misleading zeros.
      var hasRealData = data.seeded !== true && Number(data.totalLines) > 0;
      if (!hasRealData) {
        renderSeeded();
        return;
      }

      var total = Number(data.totalLines).toLocaleString();
      var today = Number(data.todayLines).toLocaleString();
      var history = data.history || [];
      var sparkline = history.length
        ? sparklineBars(history, "bg-accent/60 hover:bg-accent transition-colors")
        : '<div class="text-fg-muted text-[10px]">No history yet</div>';

      content.innerHTML =
        '<div class="space-y-2">' +
          row("~/$", total) +
          row("today", "+" + today, "text-accent text-sm font-bold") +
          '<div class="pt-2 border-t border-card-border">' +
            '<div class="flex items-end gap-[2px] h-8">' + sparkline + '</div>' +
          '</div>' +
          '<div class="text-fg-muted text-[10px] pt-1">updated ' + data.updatedAt + ' via GitHub Actions</div>' +
        '</div>';
    } catch (e) {
      renderSeeded();
    }
  }

  loadLocData();
</script>
